To rotate the matrix, you can use a transpose operation followed by a row reversal to achieve the desired 90-degree clockwise rotation.

```python
def rotate_matrix(m):
    n = len(m)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i, n):
            m[j][i], m[i][j] = m[i][j], m[j][i]
    for row in m:
        row.reverse()
    return None
```
